-- France to Send Medical Team to Jordan-Syria Border for Refugees
-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 2012-08-06T18:26:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-06/france-to-send-medical-team-to-jordan-syria-border-for-refugees.html
France is sending a military surgical
group and a medical team to  Jordan  to care for refugees from
 Syria , President  Francois Hollande  said in a statement.  The medical assistance, which has obtained Jordanian
authorization, will be sent immediately, according to todayâ€™s
statement.  Several hundred thousand refugees now are in countries
bordering Syria, of whom 120,000 are registered with the United
Nations High Commission, according to the statement.  Hollande has given the Ministry of Defense and Foreign
Affairs Ministry in coordination with the Interior Ministry
responsibility for installing the medical facilities by the end
of the week in Jordan along the Syrian frontier, the government
said.  Foreign Affairs Minister Laurent Fabius will travel to
Jordan on Aug. 15 and to other countries in the region,
according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
